        <summary>How does the federal tax bracket system work?</summary>
        <p>The US federal tax system is progressive. This means you don't pay one flat tax rate on all your income. Instead, your income is divided into chunks (brackets), and each chunk is taxed at a progressively higher rate. For example, your first $11,000 might be taxed at 10%, the next $30,000 at 12%, and so on.</p>
      </details>
