        <summary>How do tax brackets change from year to year?</summary>
        <p>The IRS adjusts tax brackets annually to account for inflation, a process known as indexing. This prevents "bracket creep," where a cost-of-living raise pushes you into a higher tax bracket without actually increasing your purchasing power.</p>
      </details>
